feedback: Nothing was as confusing as I am an avid lover of rpg games. I was a bit confused why is this game a prolific survey but I enjoyed it v much \n\nThe game felt immersive, so i was more and more curious.

I feel happy that I completed the game. Some irritation that I had to search multiple places to find the key.
I have schizoid personality disorder so feel little in the way of emotions. If anything, I feel intrigued at what this study is trying to investigate, and liked the AI generated images
The illustrations were beautiful and was a really enjoyable part of the game. Beautiful imagery makes me happy so I enjoyed playing the game.
Happiness & Joy at having found the ring. \nSlight rage because they had stolen property from my family

As Alex I'd feel very relieved and joyous that I'd gotten back what had once been stolen from my family.\n\nI had no particular striking feeling throughout the game, only at the end. I did not feel the game was engaging enough for me to develop any strong feelings on it throughout.

I felt anxious especially when I was looking for the key . I was anxious because I was afraid of getting caught. Towards the end of the game I felt relieved and excited because I had found what I was looking for .
